social_posts.post_text: I wrote On Your Way Home alone on New Year’s Eve 2021. I couldn’t make it home for the holidays, most everyone was still nervous from the state of the world and I was rounding the corner on finishing the album. I slept on the couch for a week in my buddies back house studio where I recorded the first ep - thanks @konradsollsnyder - wrote it on the High Hope piano and tracked it before the sun came up. It has been a good friend to me ever since and I’m happy to see it also has been for a lot of you too - my most streamed song this year. If you were at a State of the Heart show you’ll remember me saying even if you have no one to call - you can always call on the music. Just a reminder that’s always the case. I love this version with my best buddies @christianharger @melissafuller @travnabb and @billyjustineau - thanks to @davidmctiernan + @bram.vandermark and the @vevo team for making it happen. Thanks for listening x

You know that sensation of hearing music through the wall? The rumble and resonance of a moment just out of reach…think we’ve got a time machine with this one. Enjoy a frame of Baby, Baby 🕰️

Does the music make the moment or the moment make the music? I think a bit of both. Case study #1: “Baby, Baby” revisits 1998’s Stepmom. 

I feel like I’m still sitting in the back of my Moms Ford Windstar watching the vhs on the flip down screen. It’s a 90s soft/warm colored core memory. Maybe I couldn’t fully understand the gravity of their situation as a kid but I know I felt it as deeply as I could and that’s why it stuck. Everything over time. ⏳

ending the year with both pockets full of songs and stories, feeling eager to crusade for them - for us. i hope as we all ease into a new year that a moment is taken to be proud of exactly where you are - this life is a collaboration with yourself across a timeline where all of the labor connects and energy transfers - it’s a beautiful correspondence. you need to be here, you were always waiting for this frame to meet you. take it in and regard it. 

more on all of that soon enough. 🫀

Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays my friends! 🎄🫀 Enjoy the time with your friends and loved ones. If it happens to be a more quiet or somber one this year, know I’m always sending comfort through the music.

Regarding: Presence 

Sitting at my childhood piano with another Christmas in the book, I couldn’t help but feel a sort of absence in the air.
I think of time all of the time. I think of yesterday and who was still with us. The holidays conjure these emotions like nothing else can. It’s how the frames on the wall glow with a glitter dusted grief.
Playing the keys that have known my fingerprints forever, I got to thinking:
If it’s all memory returning then maybe it’s not an absence I’m feeling.
It’s a presence.
The gift of knowing the frames are lined up in a flip book. Connected and tethered, etched in permanent ink. The kind that sticks to you and is always in
correspondence. These are the letters of your life. To you, for you, by you. Always with you.
It’s a presence.

Regarding: Edward Hopper 
If you aren’t aware of Edward Hopper, you just don’t know you are. His iconic “Nighthawks” painting which shows customers sitting at the counter of an all-night diner has been seen by most of us. In the journey of this new creative era - Eddie’s life’s work has been a massive inspiration to me. He lived most of his days with his partner Josephine in their walk up apartment at 3 Washington Square North from 1913 until his death in 1967. I used to live right across the park. He’d ride the above ground trains to get his perspectives of the city and preferred to paint through the lens of a window. New York served as a backdrop for explorations he described as the “vast and varied realm” of one’s inner life. The way he painted left room for poetic suggestion and interpretation - much to me like a song. It was special to see his work in person today at The Whitney. I highly encourage you guys to dive into the rabbit hole that is Edward Hopper 🕳️ 🐇

So much love tethers all of the humans you see here and too many more for a 90 second reel. Regard the time. Be here now. So grateful for all of you. More moments and stories to come. We’ll all get there little by little and also in great leaps in ‘23. Love you all. Happy New Year!

“I’ll Be By Your Side” out now

“I’ll Be By Your Side” has been a true collaboration with myself across the timeline. Two weeks ago, I was working on a production for the new album from the living room of The Bowery Hotel when a note from my old dear friend @kaseytruman came through subject reading “Urgent: I’ll Be By Your Side Request”. My mind went back to a Los Angeles mid afternoon in 2016, my old acoustic on my lap and my friend @andrewheringer in the bedroom control room as he pressed record on the simple but sturdy love song that showed up for us that day. I talk about the question and the answer years often. That era had more questions than answers but I when met Andrew I knew he was asking the right ones. I used to the listen to his band Milo Greene on the roof of my New York Apartment years before we would end up somehow living across the street from each other. Little by little, we tracked the elements of this song that day. My guitar solo, Andrew’s bgvs, the piano and drums you’re hearing right now are relics. 

Longer story short - the note explained that the song was to be featured on the new series Fire Country on CBS 2/3 (tonight!). The task at hand became jumping back into that room and joining those guys to complete the circle. I sang along to the soundtrack of yesterday, added a few colors I couldn’t see back then and called @melissafuller to join the choir. @benjaminwest and @santa_clauss came through in a big way on the last lap to help me get this ready for you. I’m a lucky guy. 

This animation was done by one of my favorite artists @art.kve and it speaks to the journey and who’s on it. It’s important to include one’s own self in the picture as you are always by your side - in constant correspondence. This experience made that tangible for me. I hope you see your journey reflected in it too. 

Regarding credit post to come and be sure to catch the whole song on Fire Country tonight on CBS. Me across the entire timeline is grateful ♾️

My warmest regards to those by my side who made “I’ll Be By Your Side” possible and to all of you listening, who close the loop. The magic is in our collaboration.Co-written and co-produced with Andrew Heringer Drums by Curtis MarreroBacking Vocals by Melissa Fuller and Andrew HeringerGuitar, Bass & Keys by My Younger SelfLead Vocal, Acoustic Guitar and Additional Production by My Present Self Mixed by Dave Clauss with assistance from Benjamin WestMastered by Ruairi O’FlahertyCover photo and design by Audrey Ventura Animation by Kelly Emmrich Special thank you to Kasey Truman, Devin Sarno, Sam Riddle, Isaac Green, Aaron Bay-Schuck & the Warner Records team.We’ll always find each other on memory lane.Race you there.

Today marks the two year anniversary of State of the Heart. This Friday, “Go Getter” will usher in a new era — album two is coming. The dream is alive and well, and many thanks to you all for being with me on the journey down the rabbit hole, connecting our dots all across the timeline. Pre-save in bio — Race you there. 🕳️🐇

When Eadweard Muybridge took a series of individual photographs and put them in sequence, the motion picture was created — and with it, the notion that a single frame of an action could capture the essence of the whole movement. If you consider the present moment through the same lens, it would be tethered to the entirety of your life’s motion picture. This is the movie. 
 
When I started incorporating Regarding into everything I do, it was to give a deeper context. When you review the tape and connect your dots, you’re heading toward a powerful source: the Why. When you practice the act of Regarding time, I believe you’re in correspondence with yourself across the timeline. Maybe intuition is just remembering ahead. The dream dreamt really does get delivered.
 
“Go Getter” is the invitation to jump down the rabbit hole. To ask the questions, repair the frames… to go get your memories. I wrote it in a flash of intuition in the middle of the night, brought it to life with my brothers @jongreen1979 and @benjaminwest then went back to landmark corners of my life, empty rooms full of memories, and created my favorite piece of work yet with my brother @splitthemoon - We adventured together, following the thread from New York to my hometown of Lancaster, PA. This era is all about what we’re really trying to say. Why we’re really here. To rewind, please remember. ♾️📼

Make sure to check out the video — there’s more than meets the eye.

Tour. Is. Happening! This Fall we are taking the new record out on the road starting at The Royale in Boston and winding up back at a very special venue to my heart, Webster Hall in New York City.

I have a feeling this is going to be one for the memories. I’ll be joined by one of my favorite new artists @ceciliacastleman - Pre-sale starts Wednesday and tickets go live Friday 9am local time.

When I finished the album a few weeks ago I needed something to obsess over…so I told my friends at the label that I’d edit a video for “Caroline” myself. Having the stellar footage from my brother @splitthemoon and studio clips from @tyleroaks made the job way easier. It was a meditative process and I found a lot of parallels to music editing. Thanks for so much love on this song on its first two days, it is such a thrill to announce this record, the subtitles for feelings perspective and the tour. Would love to take a moment to thank my collaborators - I always wanted to write “Caroline” and after a whirlwind week in the Scottish Highlands making music with my fellow Irish brother @foyvance I knew he was my partner for it. He’s singing backgrounds on these chorus’s. It’s a real full circle moment to share with him - I first discovered Foy at a life changing Webster Hall set in 2011 so it’s fitting we’re playing there on the tour. We have a few more special records on the project I can’t wait for you to hear. I brought the goods to @butchwalker and knew we’d have a special production collaboration. I first discovered Butch after hearing “Mixtape” on One Tree Hill in high school. That piano you hear me playing on is the same one from that song. Talk about a soundtrack. Very special to work with Butch. A huge thanks to @travnabb for being one of the best drummers in the world. @smoffitt13 has been mixing my music Since Brooklyn™️ and I’m so grateful we are continuing the journey together on this album. He and I tweak to the very last moment and I love him for that - he never let’s go until it’s the most authentic representation of the intention. He never ceases to amaze me. “Caroline” and the whole record was mastered by another Irishman Ruairi O’Flaherty @nomograph.mastering and I couldn’t imagine it in better hands - his intentionality is unmatched. Clearly I have an amazing crew making me look good and I’m grateful for that. Love you guys for the support and go check out the whole video, I loved putting this New York love letter together.

I like the phrase “catch feelings” because it hints at the idea that they come from a higher place-the source. One of those core feelings that often slips through our hands is freedom. I feel free when I am truly in the present moment. It’s impossible to stay there, but we do get these glimpses, like poetry in motion, of an ordinary frame turned extraordinary simply because you know you’re in it. This is a subtitle I hope you read from the record. I think of the way a bird soars through the sky or how evening light paints the downtown concrete on a walk home after checking on all of your people. I’ve been taking these videos as my way of checking into the moments around me. I put them together and was moved at how seeminglv random frames connect to the same film - this Life movie. All to say, “Free” is my way of carrying a little peace in my pocket, and I hope it travels well with you, too.
Big thanks to @jongreen1979 for being in the moment with me to discover this song and to produce with me alongside our brother @benjaminwest - my truly dear friend  @thisisruthanne for her incredible vocals - @smoffitt13 as always for another gorgeous mix - @nomograph.mastering for making it feel a final feeling - and to @splitthemoon for capturing the tree from home so perfectly.

(the secret’s in the subtitles)

What can I say? This album is my life’s work - an accumulation and translation of feelings from the film I get to call my own. I couldn’t be more proud of it and the connection it’s gifted me. The experience has been so profound, I don’t think this project could feel any more successful than it does right now - no matter what happens. It helps me laugh, cry, dance, cope and more than anything has helped me to understand that the gift is to getting to know yourself - it’s the present. Subtitles started with my brother @conordroney and his words “I’m happy for you” spoken at 2am in a kitchen upstate after a conversation only siblings could translate. I want you all to enjoy your lives, recognize the moments as you get to experience them. I want you to enjoy your movie. The album is out tomorrow night and I appreciate this time and space we’ve found together so much.

It’s opening weekend…Get in the car, we’re going to the movies 🎬

Do you ever feel like your life is just like a movie? It’s because it is the movie. All these people around me right now are living their different stories, their films making sense of as it they go, and so am i. I wrote an album called subtitles for feelings, about just that. Going back in time, with context, rewinding the tape. And translating the subtitles of the scenes in your life for what they’re really trying to say. Even right now, I don’t know what this really means, but I’m on a hunch; my intuition is remembering ahead that I’m supposed to be here. I’m gonna look back, rewind the tape, make sense of it. It’s gonna be a grand title. All to say I hope you enjoy your movie, rewind the tape. All you gotta do is remember. My album Subtitles For Feelings is out now 🎞️

Remember the feeling when you were a kid and all you wanted was to ride shotgun with your parents? You were fully prepared to take on the responsibility of navigator and DJ. For late night trips, your charge was keeping the conversation alive and running into the convenience store for the goods while Mom or Dad put gas in the car. You understood the importance. So when your finger suddenly slipped from the play to fast forward button and you found yourself behind the wheel, you already knew it was all about that seat next to you. 
 
Subtitles is a tapestry of timelines intersecting. It’s been an unbelievable gift sharing and bringing this concept to life with my family and friends. Every day was a new revelation... especially for me and my brother @conordroney - my original Shotgun Rider. Every day we jump the wormhole and come back better for it. If Subtitles means anything to you, Conor is an important person to thank. 
 
“Shotgun Rider” means so much to me because it represents this feeling. This video is my EIGHTH collaboration with @splitthemoon - We share the same birthday and the subtitles we translate together are essential ones. When I think of The Movie, I think of Gus and his camera. I want to thank my amazing friend @mroxburgh for jumping into the scene and making my 90s Full-House-meets-New York dream come alive. This was a motley crew and we laughed for two days straight. 
 
I have so many people to thank and a Regarding post and unfolding of this entire project is to come - but I wanted to take a second to thank my true friend @jongreen1979 for not only writing and recording this song with me but also for spending the better part of a year day after day, song reveal after song reveal… and bagel after bagel… bringing this music to life. (Often in his Stone Pony Asbury Park hoodie, so of course it’s only right that today marks 48 years since Born to Run was released.) It was a dream, Jon. Thank you to @benjaminwest , who lifted us to the finish line like only he can, just as he did with State of the Heart, and to my brother @butchwalker - it was full circle getting to work with a hero. There’s so much more to come down the road. Enjoy the ride.

Tonight is a #superbluemoon, not to be seen again until 2037. Maybe, once in a blue moon, you notice something like a dedication plaque on the park bench you’re sitting on or walking past.
 
These etched intentions have been there all along, quietly but permanently keeping memories alive - supernovas frozen in time and space. I took a walk around today to collect some. I try to read them whenever I can - it’s my way of hitting play on a scene in another movie. Even if it’s a short loop, it’s someone’s shared time and therefore worth mine. A beautiful happening occurs - I always seem to walk away with more love. The tether connects, and that intention is echoed a little louder into the ether. 
 
“Little Supernovas” is a reminder to read the dedication, take the snapshot of the ordinary moment, and try to get a sneak peek at the subtitle in real-time.

Last night, the band and I — along with 1,400 Shotgun Riders — sold out Webster Hall in New York City. With my old college ID in my pocket and in the fever dream of it all, I swear I saw my younger self in the crowd a few times. I walked for miles and miles through the city today to keep my ringing ears company. Memory lane was everywhere I turned. I used to live across the street from Webster back in my NYU days, where so much life was lived in such a short time over a decade ago. So many questions to live through. I used to play the old basement at Webster and write down main stage manifestations. 

Last night, as I was singing “Poems,” I envisioned the park bench just a few blocks away that I carved my initials on so many years ago. I went back today and they’re still there. Underneath the extra coats of paint, you can still make out the impression of “PD” above a new dedication plaque. It reads “Eddie Williams, Photographer & Messenger” with the quote “Take it easy My Youth.” …I can’t make it up. Sounds like he was a real Go Getter. 

Last night was the loudest message received. It was incredible to have my Dad back on stage with me, my Brother introducing “My Grandfather’s Home,” this incredible band full of history alongside me, and Cecilia bringing total magic to the room. I’ll have more to say as I’m still walking through it, but for now — thank you to each and every one of you who showed up last night and on this entire first leg of the tour. I really love you guys. ♾️

Seen to Scene: I’ve been filming about as much as I’ve been scoring the movie lately. Creating Subtitles for Feelings taught me that every moment is a scene in life’s emotion picture. So I’ve been noticing the moments and finding immense joy capturing them. It’s nice to have something outside of music that still feels like music to me. I love the buzz of connecting sound and picture. 

I really just want to start sharing more colors, and hope they inspire you to notice in your own way. Here are two scenes of the same sentiment - I’m here for you.
